			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The NES has two entirely disjoint regions of memory. One for the CPU, one for the PPU.<br /><br />Games can be divided into two types: those that had two separate fixed memories (e.g. Super Mario Bros.), and those that had one fixed memory and used RAM for the PPU.<br /><br />If RAM is used for the PPU, then the CPU has to copy the data to the PPU to be able to show anything. Furthermore, then there's no particular restriction of where in memory the tile data is stored, or even that it's stored uncompressed.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
